File: Stage 4 load-shedding will continue on Friday with lower stages of power outages expected for the weekend. JOHANNESBURG - Stage 4 load-shedding will continue until Friday evening. Eskom says it will then implement lower stages for the weekend.
Electricity demand is said to be less on weekends. LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you The utility is also expecting some of its generation units to return to service. Eskom, however, warns that changes to the load-shedding stages may apply at short notice. READ: Load-shedding to continue until further notice Eskom implemented Stage 4 load-shedding earlier this week after its Koeberg Unit tripped. The unit is expected to be back on the grid on Saturday. South Africans are urged to continue using electricity sparingly.